laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid filled and abnormally enlarged, measuring up to 12 mm in diameter, with wall thickening and hyperemia, compatible with acute appendicitis. The rest of the abdominal and pelvic organs are normal. There is a small amount of fluid in the right aspect of the pelvis, possibly small free fluid or right hydrosalpinx, and a 2.6 x 2.4 cm cystic structure in the left aspect of the pelvis, likely of ovarian origin.
